Current Question Text: Pap Test. Also known as Pap smear or cervical cytology. A healthcare provider used a plastic or metal instrument called a speculum to open your vagina, and used a 	soft brush or plastic spatula to collect cells from your cervix. The cells were checked for cancer or signs that they may become cancer.
